column8: If this frequent waking continues with Theo, I think we need to consider moving Charlie’s crib to the nursery to separate them. That way we can do the SITBACK method with Theo. Allowing him time to cry and be observed before immediately picking him up.  At 4:30ish he woke up crying. I think it may have been due to me flushing the toilet in the guest room (or it was a coincidence). Jim tried putting him down a few times. Then I rocked him 2x, but each time he woke up within a few minutes crying  The last time I gave him about 30 seconds of crying (he was decently upset). Charlie didn’t stir at all. He stopped crying, had his eyes open for a little bit, then went to sleep on his own.   It is super important that we don’t teach Theo bad sleep habits with the rocking because we are trying to quiet him to keep Charlie sleeping.   Also if Theo seems really hungry during the day we should give him as much as he wants. He may be going through a growth spurt as well.

Highly restless around 820 needed to be soothed back to sleep. Also woke at 950 needing to be held. Would not be put down after night feeding without being held for 20 sec.   Theo was put to sleep awake... Maybe this is the start of sleep regression?
